<TITLE> Mohammedan, Brothers close gaps with leaders Abahani </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 18 (bdnwes24.com) Giants Dhaka Mohammedan Sporting Club and Brothers Union closed gaps with leaders Dhaka Abahani Limited, in contrast, in their first-leg last match in the Citycell B. League on Thursday. Brothers Union routed Farashganj Sporting Club 4-0 at Bangabandhu National Stadium while Dhaka Mohammedan managed a hard-fought 1-0 win over hosts Khulna Abahani Krira Chakra at Khulna Stadium. Away at MA Aziz Stadium, hosts Chittagong Abahani Limited recorded a convincing 4-0 win over visitors Arambagh Krira Sangha as the B. League resumed on Thursday following an 11-day break for Eid-ul-Azha. After the 10th round, Mohammedan and Brothers Union were jointly in the second position with 19 points each, three points behind league leaders Abahani Limited. Chittagong Abahani raised their point tally to 13 from 10 outings while Farashganj, Arambagh and Khulna Abahani stuck to their previous points of 12, nine and three respectively playing 10 games. At BNS, Brothers faced no problem against Farashganj as Ghanaian striker Henry Quaye being set by striker Mehdi Hasan Tupu gave the Gopibahgh-based outfit a lead in the 23rd minute and doubled the margin eight minutes later with a fine volley. Nigerian striker Chibuke Divine headed a Motiur Munna corner home to make it 3-0 in the stoppage time before the lemon break and Rezaul Karim Liton sealed the match from a free kick 10 minutes from time. In Khulna, Egyptian medio Hazem Mahmoud Khaled rescued the popular black and white outfit striking in the 34th minute and the lone goal was good enough for the visitors to see off hosts Khulna Abahani. In Chittagong, hosts Abahani were 1-0 up in the first half against Arambagh as striker Mithun Chowdhury put the hosts ahead in the 21st minute. After resumption, Arambagh saw its defender Mostafa Kaba struck a own goal seven minutes into the second half while Rony slotted two goals in the 57th and 76th minute to ensure Abahani's home win. bd
